benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/availableBasePlans - Retrieve available base plans

covered: Successful retrieval of all available base plans without accountId (TC01)
Retrieval when no base plans exist (TC03)
Regression test for empty array response (TC14)
Security tests for SQL injection (TC12) and XSS (TC13)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested.
No explicit tests for caching headers or cache validation.
Rate limiting or throttling scenarios are not covered.
No tests explicitly verify authorization beyond token presence (e.g., role-based access).
No explicit tests for performance under peak load (concurrent requests, large payloads).
No tests for response content validation beyond presence of fields (e.g., data correctness).
No tests for handling of unsupported or extra query parameters beyond ignoring them.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large datasets and proper response structure.
Include tests for caching headers such as ETag and Cache-Control to ensure proper caching behavior.
Implement rate limiting/throttling tests to verify system stability under high request volume.
Add authorization role-based access tests to ensure only permitted users can access the endpoint.
Create performance tests under peak load and large payload scenarios.
Verify response content accuracy and completeness beyond just structure.
Test handling of unsupported query parameters explicitly to confirm graceful ignoring or error responses.
